    <h2>Meet the graduate</h2>
<p>&quot;As a graduate at TfL, you have a variety of opportunities to develop on top of your day-to-day responsibilities. This could be representing TfL at external events; for example, I spoke to students at Lewisham College and Bullers Wood School about my experiences. I also had the opportunity to facilitate at an Asset Management Forum, attended by businesses from all over the UK providing a fantastic networking opportunity.</p>
<p>I have been encouraged to develop myself professionally through a number of useful training courses. When you start the graduate scheme, you will be given a list of graduate specific training courses that you need to complete; for example, presentation skills and managing finance. There are also opportunities to take part in training courses outside of those specifically assigned to graduates; for example, when I wanted to improve my coaching skills, I was able to attend a course to develop this area.&quot;</p>
<p><strong>- John, Strategy &amp; Change Management Graduate</strong></p> 
 </div>
